{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbeb35e69-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s9412"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9412"},"text":"§ 9412.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this chapter:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbeb35e6a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s9412/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of Health and Human Services.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbeb35e6b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s9412/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “State” includes (in addition to the fifty States) the District of Columbia, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands, Guam, American Samoa, the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands, and the Northern Mariana Islands.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbeb35e6c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s9412/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “nonprofit”, as applied to any entity, means an entity which is owned and operated by one or more corporations or associations no part of the net earnings of which inures or may lawfully inure to the benefit of any private shareholder or person.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbeb35e6d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/398/tI/s102"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–398, title I, § 102","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-07"},"text":"Oct. 7, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1569"},"text":"94 Stat. 1569","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/tIX/s902/f/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, title IX, § 902(f)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", (C), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/560"},"text":"95 Stat. 560","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbeb35e6e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbeb35e6f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbeb35e70-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/398"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–398","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-10-07"},"text":"Oct. 7, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1564"},"text":"94 Stat. 1564","children":[],"tail":", known as the Mental Health Systems Act, which enacted this chapter, amended sections 210, 225a, 229b, 242a, 246, 289k–1, 300"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–2, 300m–2, 1396b, 2689a to 2689c, 2689e, 2689g, and 2689h of this title, repealed "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2689q"},"text":"section 2689q of this title","children":[],"tail":", and enacted provisions set out as notes under sections 242a, 246, 289k–1, and 2689b of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s9401"},"text":"section 9401 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbeb35e71-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1981—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35","children":[],"tail":" redesignated former par. (5) as (3). Former pars. (3), (4), (6), and (7), which defined “State mental health authority”, “mental health service area”, “priority population group”, and “Governor”, respectively, were struck out."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbeb35e72-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbeb35e73-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1981 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1981","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s902/h"},"text":"section 902(h) of Pub. L. 97–35","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under section 238"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":" of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n